2098 // Configuration for C calling convention (see c-linkage.cc).
2099 #define PARAM_REGISTERS a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7
2100 #define RETURN_REGISTER a0
2101 #define FP_PARAM_REGISTERS f0, f1, f2, f3, f4, f5, f6, f7
2102 #define FP_RETURN_REGISTER f0
2103 
2104 void Simulator::CallAnyCTypeFunction(Address target_address,
2105  const EncodedCSignature& signature) {
2106  const int64_t* stack_pointer = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(get_register(sp));
2107  const double* double_stack_pointer =
2108  reinterpret_cast<double*>(get_register(sp));
2109 
2110  const Register kParamRegisters[] = {PARAM_REGISTERS};
2111  const FPURegister kFPParamRegisters[] = {FP_PARAM_REGISTERS};
2112 
2113  int num_gp_params = 0, num_fp_params = 0, num_stack_params = 0;
2114 
2115  CHECK_LE(signature.ParameterCount(), kMaxCParameters);
2116  static_assert(sizeof(AnyCType) == 8, "AnyCType is assumed to be 64-bit.");
2117  AnyCType args[kMaxCParameters];
2118  for (int i = 0; i < signature.ParameterCount(); ++i) {
2119  if (signature.IsFloat(i)) {
2120  if (num_fp_params < 8) {
2121  args[i].double_value =
2122  get_fpu_register_double(kFPParamRegisters[num_fp_params++]);
2123  } else if (num_gp_params < 8) {
2124  args[i].int64_value = get_register(kParamRegisters[num_gp_params++]);
2125  } else {
2126  args[i].double_value = double_stack_pointer[num_stack_params++];
2127  }
2128  } else {
2129  if (num_gp_params < 8) {
2130  args[i].int64_value = get_register(kParamRegisters[num_gp_params++]);
2131  } else {
2132  args[i].int64_value = stack_pointer[num_stack_params++];
2133  }
2134  }
2135  }
2136  AnyCType result;
2137  GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT(CALL_TARGET_VARARG)
2138  /* else */ {
2139  UNREACHABLE();
2140  }
2141  static_assert(20 == kMaxCParameters,
2142  "If you've changed kMaxCParameters, please change the "
2143  "GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT macro.");
2144 
2145 #undef CALL_TARGET_VARARG
2146 #undef CALL_ARGS
2147 #undef GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT
2148 
2149  if (signature.IsReturnFloat()) {
2150  set_fpu_register_double(FP_RETURN_REGISTER, result.double_value);
2151  } else {
2152  set_register(RETURN_REGISTER, result.int64_value);
2153  }
2154 }
2155 
2156 #undef PARAM_REGISTERS
2157 #undef RETURN_REGISTER
2158 #undef FP_PARAM_REGISTERS
2159 #undef FP_RETURN_REGISTER
2160 
2161 // Software interrupt instructions are used by the simulator to call into the
2162 // C-based V8 runtime. They are also used for debugging with simulator.
2163 void Simulator::SoftwareInterrupt() {
2164  int32_t opcode_hi15 = instr_.Bits(31, 17);
2165  CHECK_EQ(opcode_hi15, 0x15);
2166  uint32_t code = instr_.Bits(14, 0);
2167  // We first check if we met a call_rt_redirected.
2168  if (instr_.InstructionBits() == rtCallRedirInstr) {
2169  Redirection* redirection = Redirection::FromInstruction(instr_.instr());
2170 
2171  // This is dodgy but it works because the C entry stubs are never moved.
2172  int64_t saved_ra = get_register(ra);
2173  intptr_t external =
2174  reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(redirection->external_function());
2175 
2176  Address func_addr =
2177  reinterpret_cast<Address>(redirection->external_function());
2178  SimulatorData* simulator_data = isolate_->simulator_data();
2179  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(simulator_data);
2180  const EncodedCSignature& signature =
2181  simulator_data->GetSignatureForTarget(func_addr);
2182  if (signature.IsValid()) {
2183  CHECK_EQ(redirection->type(), ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL);
2184  CallAnyCTypeFunction(external, signature);
2185  set_register(ra, saved_ra);
2186  set_pc(get_register(ra));
2187  return;
2188  }
2189 
2190  int64_t* stack_pointer = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(get_register(sp));
2191 
2192  int64_t arg0 = get_register(a0);
2193  int64_t arg1 = get_register(a1);
2194  int64_t arg2 = get_register(a2);
2195  int64_t arg3 = get_register(a3);
2196  int64_t arg4 = get_register(a4);
2197  int64_t arg5 = get_register(a5);
2198  int64_t arg6 = get_register(a6);
2199  int64_t arg7 = get_register(a7);
2200  int64_t arg8 = stack_pointer[0];
2201  int64_t arg9 = stack_pointer[1];
2202  int64_t arg10 = stack_pointer[2];
2203  int64_t arg11 = stack_pointer[3];
2204  int64_t arg12 = stack_pointer[4];
2205  int64_t arg13 = stack_pointer[5];
2206  int64_t arg14 = stack_pointer[6];
2207  int64_t arg15 = stack_pointer[7];
2208  int64_t arg16 = stack_pointer[8];
2209  int64_t arg17 = stack_pointer[9];
2210  int64_t arg18 = stack_pointer[10];
2211  int64_t arg19 = stack_pointer[11];
2212  static_assert(kMaxCParameters == 20);
2213 
2214  bool fp_call =
2215  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL) ||
2216  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL) ||
2217  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL) ||
2218  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL) ||
2219  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL);
2220 
2221  // Based on CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FPU), Loong64 will use either hardware
2222  // FPU, or gcc soft-float routines. Hardware FPU is simulated in this
2223  // simulator. Soft-float has additional abstraction of ExternalReference,
2224  // to support serialization.
2225  if (fp_call) {
2226  double dval0, dval1; // one or two double parameters
2227  int32_t ival; // zero or one integer parameters
2228  int64_t iresult = 0; // integer return value
2229  double dresult = 0; // double return value
2230  GetFpArgs(&dval0, &dval1, &ival);
2231  SimulatorRuntimeCall generic_target =
2232  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeCall>(external);
2233  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2234  switch (redirection->type()) {
2235  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL:
2236  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL:
2237  PrintF("Call to host function at %p with args %f, %f",
2238  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
2239  dval0, dval1);
2240  break;
2241  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL:
2242  PrintF("Call to host function at %p with arg %f",
2243  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
2244  dval0);
2245  break;
2246  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL:
2247  PrintF("Call to host function at %p with args %f, %d",
2248  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
2249  dval0, ival);
2250  break;
2251  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL:
2252  PrintF("Call to host function at %p with args %f",
2253  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
2254  dval0);
2255  break;
2256  default:
2257  UNREACHABLE();
2258  }
2259  }
2260  switch (redirection->type()) {
2261  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL: {
2262  SimulatorRuntimeCompareCall target =
2263  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeCompareCall>(external);
2264  iresult = target(dval0, dval1);
2265  set_register(v0, static_cast<int64_t>(iresult));
2266  // set_register(v1, static_cast<int64_t>(iresult >> 32));
2267  break;
2268  }
2269  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL: {
2270  SimulatorRuntimeFPFPCall target =
2271  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPFPCall>(external);
2272  dresult = target(dval0, dval1);
2273  SetFpResult(dresult);
2274  break;
2275  }
2276  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL: {
2277  SimulatorRuntimeFPCall target =
2278  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPCall>(external);
2279  dresult = target(dval0);
2280  SetFpResult(dresult);
2281  break;
2282  }
2283  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL: {
2284  SimulatorRuntimeFPIntCall target =
2285  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPIntCall>(external);
2286  dresult = target(dval0, ival);
2287  SetFpResult(dresult);
2288  break;
2289  }
2290  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL: {
2291  SimulatorRuntimeIntFPCall target =
2292  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeIntFPCall>(external);
2293  iresult = target(dval0);
2294  set_register(a0, static_cast<int64_t>(iresult));
2295  break;
2296  }
2297  default:
2298  UNREACHABLE();
2299  }
2300  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2301  switch (redirection->type()) {
2302  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL:
2303  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL:
2304  PrintF("Returned %08x\n", static_cast<int32_t>(iresult));
2305  break;
2306  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL:
2307  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL:
2308  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL:
2309  PrintF("Returned %f\n", dresult);
2310  break;
2311  default:
2312  UNREACHABLE();
2313  }
2314  }
2315  } else if (redirection->type() ==
2316  ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_POINTER_CALL) {
2317  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2318  PrintF("Call to host function at %p args %08" PRIx64 " \n",
2319  reinterpret_cast<void*>(external), arg0);
2320  }
2321  SimulatorRuntimeFPTaggedCall target =
2322  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPTaggedCall>(external);
2323  double dresult = target(arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3);
2324  SetFpResult(dresult);
2325  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2326  PrintF("Returned %f\n", dresult);
2327  }
2328  } else if (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL) {
2329  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2330  PrintF("Call to host function at %p args %08" PRIx64 " \n",
2331  reinterpret_cast<void*>(external), arg0);
2332  }
2333  SimulatorRuntimeDirectApiCall target =
2334  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeDirectApiCall>(external);
2335  target(arg0);
2336  } else if (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::DIRECT_GETTER_CALL) {
2337  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2338  PrintF("Call to host function at %p args %08" PRIx64 " %08" PRIx64
2339  " \n",
2340  reinterpret_cast<void*>(external), arg0, arg1);
2341  }
2342  SimulatorRuntimeDirectGetterCall target =
2343  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeDirectGetterCall>(external);
2344  target(arg0, arg1);
2345  } else {
2346  DCHECK(redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_CALL ||
2347  redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_CALL_PAIR);
2348  SimulatorRuntimeCall target =
2349  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeCall>(external);
2350  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2351  PrintF(
2352  "Call to host function at %p "
2353  "args %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64
2354  " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64
2355  " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64
2356  " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64
2357  " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64 " , %08" PRIx64
2358  " \n",
2359  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(target)), arg0, arg1, arg2,
2360  arg3, arg4, arg5, arg6, arg7, arg8, arg9, arg10, arg11, arg12,
2361  arg13, arg14, arg15, arg16, arg17, arg18, arg19);
2362  }
2363  ObjectPair result = target(arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4, arg5, arg6, arg7,
2364  arg8, arg9, arg10, arg11, arg12, arg13, arg14,
2365  arg15, arg16, arg17, arg18, arg19);
2366  set_register(v0, (int64_t)(result.x));
2367  set_register(v1, (int64_t)(result.y));
2368  }
2369  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
2370  PrintF("Returned %08" PRIx64 " : %08" PRIx64 " \n", get_register(v1),
2371  get_register(v0));
2372  }
2373  set_register(ra, saved_ra);
2374  set_pc(get_register(ra));
2375 
2376  } else if (code <= kMaxStopCode) {
2377  if (IsWatchpoint(code)) {
2378  PrintWatchpoint(code);
2379  } else {
2380  IncreaseStopCounter(code);
2381  HandleStop(code, instr_.instr());
2382  }
2383  } else {
2384  // All remaining break_ codes, and all traps are handled here.
2385  Loong64Debugger dbg(this);
2386  dbg.Debug();
2387  }
2388 }
2389 
2390 // Stop helper functions.
2391 bool Simulator::IsWatchpoint(uint64_t code) {
2392  return (code <= kMaxWatchpointCode);
2393 }
2394 
2395 void Simulator::PrintWatchpoint(uint64_t code) {
2396  Loong64Debugger dbg(this);
2397  ++break_count_;
2398  PrintF("\n---- break %" PRId64 " marker: %3d (instr count: %8" PRId64
2399  " ) ----------"
2400  "----------------------------------",
2401  code, break_count_, icount_);
2402  dbg.PrintAllRegs(); // Print registers and continue running.
2403 }
2404 
2405 void Simulator::HandleStop(uint64_t code, Instruction* instr) {
2406  // Stop if it is enabled, otherwise go on jumping over the stop
2407  // and the message address.
2408  if (IsEnabledStop(code)) {
2409  Loong64Debugger dbg(this);
2410  dbg.Stop(instr);
2411  }
2412 }
2413 
2414 bool Simulator::IsStopInstruction(Instruction* instr) {
2415  int32_t opcode_hi15 = instr->Bits(31, 17);
2416  uint32_t code = static_cast<uint32_t>(instr->Bits(14, 0));
2417  return (opcode_hi15 == 0x15) && code > kMaxWatchpointCode &&
2418  code <= kMaxStopCode;
2419 }
2420 
2421 bool Simulator::IsEnabledStop(uint64_t code) {
2422  DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
2423  DCHECK_GT(code, kMaxWatchpointCode);
2424  return !(watched_stops_[code].count & kStopDisabledBit);
2425 }
2426 
2427 void Simulator::EnableStop(uint64_t code) {
2428  if (!IsEnabledStop(code)) {
2429  watched_stops_[code].count &= ~kStopDisabledBit;
2430  }
2431 }
2432 
2433 void Simulator::DisableStop(uint64_t code) {
2434  if (IsEnabledStop(code)) {
2435  watched_stops_[code].count |= kStopDisabledBit;
2436  }
2437 }
2438 
2439 void Simulator::IncreaseStopCounter(uint64_t code) {
2440  DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
2441  if ((watched_stops_[code].count & ~(1 << 31)) == 0x7FFFFFFF) {
2442  PrintF("Stop counter for code %" PRId64
2443  " has overflowed.\n"
2444  "Enabling this code and reseting the counter to 0.\n",
2445  code);
2446  watched_stops_[code].count = 0;
2447  EnableStop(code);
2448  } else {
2449  watched_stops_[code].count++;
2450  }
2451 }
2452 
2453 // Print a stop status.
2454 void Simulator::PrintStopInfo(uint64_t code) {
2455  if (code <= kMaxWatchpointCode) {
2456  PrintF("That is a watchpoint, not a stop.\n");
2457  return;
2458  } else if (code > kMaxStopCode) {
2459  PrintF("Code too large, only %u stops can be used\n", kMaxStopCode + 1);
2460  return;
2461  }
2462  const char* state = IsEnabledStop(code) ? "Enabled" : "Disabled";
2463  int32_t count = watched_stops_[code].count & ~kStopDisabledBit;
2464  // Don't print the state of unused breakpoints.
2465  if (count != 0) {
2466  if (watched_stops_[code].desc) {
2467  PrintF("stop %" PRId64 " - 0x%" PRIx64 " : \t%s, \tcounter = %i, \t%s\n",
2468  code, code, state, count, watched_stops_[code].desc);
2469  } else {
2470  PrintF("stop %" PRId64 " - 0x%" PRIx64 " : \t%s, \tcounter = %i\n", code,
2471  code, state, count);
2472  }
2473  }
2474 }
2475 
2476 void Simulator::SignalException(Exception e) {
2477  FATAL("Error: Exception %i raised.", static_cast<int>(e));
2478 }
2479 
2480 template <typename T>
2481 static T FPAbs(T a);
2482 
2483 template <>
2484 double FPAbs<double>(double a) {
2485  return fabs(a);
2486 }
2487 
2488 template <>
2489 float FPAbs<float>(float a) {
2490  return fabsf(a);
2491 }
2492 
2493 template <typename T>
2494 static bool FPUProcessNaNsAndZeros(T a, T b, MaxMinKind kind, T* result) {
2495  if (std::isnan(a) && std::isnan(b)) {
2496  *result = a;
2497  } else if (std::isnan(a)) {
2498  *result = b;
2499  } else if (std::isnan(b)) {
2500  *result = a;
2501  } else if (b == a) {
2502  // Handle -0.0 == 0.0 case.
2503  // std::signbit() returns int 0 or 1 so subtracting MaxMinKind::kMax
2504  // negates the result.
2505  *result = std::signbit(b) - static_cast<int>(kind) ? b : a;
2506  } else {
2507  return false;
2508  }
2509  return true;
2510 }
2511 
2512 template <typename T>
2513 static T FPUMin(T a, T b) {
2514  T result;
2515  if (FPUProcessNaNsAndZeros(a, b, MaxMinKind::kMin, &result)) {
2516  return result;
2517  } else {
2518  return b < a ? b : a;
2519  }
2520 }
2521 
2522 template <typename T>
2523 static T FPUMax(T a, T b) {
2524  T result;
2525  if (FPUProcessNaNsAndZeros(a, b, MaxMinKind::kMax, &result)) {
2526  return result;
2527  } else {
2528  return b > a ? b : a;
2529  }
2530 }
2531 
2532 template <typename T>
2533 static T FPUMinA(T a, T b) {
2534  T result;
2535  if (!FPUProcessNaNsAndZeros(a, b, MaxMinKind::kMin, &result)) {
2536  if (FPAbs(a) < FPAbs(b)) {
2537  result = a;
2538  } else if (FPAbs(b) < FPAbs(a)) {
2539  result = b;
2540  } else {
2541  result = a < b ? a : b;
2542  }
2543  }
2544  return result;
2545 }
2546 
2547 template <typename T>
2548 static T FPUMaxA(T a, T b) {
2549  T result;
2550  if (!FPUProcessNaNsAndZeros(a, b, MaxMinKind::kMin, &result)) {
2551  if (FPAbs(a) > FPAbs(b)) {
2552  result = a;
2553  } else if (FPAbs(b) > FPAbs(a)) {
2554  result = b;
2555  } else {
2556  result = a > b ? a : b;
2557  }
2558  }
2559  return result;
2560 }
2561 
2562 enum class KeepSign : bool { no = false, yes };
2563 
2564 template <typename T,
2565  typename std::enable_if_t<std::is_floating_point_v<T>, int> = 0>
2566 T FPUCanonalizeNaNArg(T result, T arg, KeepSign keepSign = KeepSign::no) {
2567  DCHECK(std::isnan(arg));
2568  T qNaN = std::numeric_limits<T>::quiet_NaN();
2569  if (keepSign == KeepSign::yes) {
2570  return std::copysign(qNaN, result);
2571  }
2572  return qNaN;
2573 }
2574 
2575 template <typename T>
2576 T FPUCanonalizeNaNArgs(T result, KeepSign keepSign, T first) {
2577  if (std::isnan(first)) {
2578  return FPUCanonalizeNaNArg(result, first, keepSign);
2579  }
2580  return result;
2581 }
2582 
2583 template <typename T, typename... Args>
2584 T FPUCanonalizeNaNArgs(T result, KeepSign keepSign, T first, Args... args) {
2585  if (std::isnan(first)) {
2586  return FPUCanonalizeNaNArg(result, first, keepSign);
2587  }
2588  return FPUCanonalizeNaNArgs(result, keepSign, args...);
2589 }
2590 
2591 template <typename Func, typename T, typename... Args>
2592 T FPUCanonalizeOperation(Func f, T first, Args... args) {
2593  return FPUCanonalizeOperation(f, KeepSign::no, first, args...);
2594 }
2595 
2596 template <typename Func, typename T, typename... Args>
2597 T FPUCanonalizeOperation(Func f, KeepSign keepSign, T first, Args... args) {
2598  T result = f(first, args...);
2599  if (std::isnan(result)) {
2600  result = FPUCanonalizeNaNArgs(result, keepSign, first, args...);
2601  }
2602  return result;
2603 }
2604 
2605 template <typename T>
2606 T FPProcessNaNBinop(T fp_lhs, T fp_rhs,
2607  const std::function<T(T, T)>& op_for_non_nan) {
2608  DCHECK(sizeof(T) == 4 || sizeof(T) == 8);
2609  typedef
2610  typename std::conditional<sizeof(T) == 4, Float32, Float64>::type FloatT;
2611  typedef
2612  typename std::conditional<sizeof(T) == 4, uint32_t, uint64_t>::type UintT;
2613 
2614  FloatT lhs = FloatT::FromBits(base::bit_cast<UintT>(fp_lhs));
2615  FloatT rhs = FloatT::FromBits(base::bit_cast<UintT>(fp_rhs));
2616  if (lhs.is_nan() && !lhs.is_quiet_nan())
2617  return lhs.to_quiet_nan().get_scalar();
2618  if (rhs.is_nan() && !rhs.is_quiet_nan())
2619  return rhs.to_quiet_nan().get_scalar();
2620 
2621  if (lhs.is_nan()) return lhs.get_scalar();
2622  if (rhs.is_nan()) return rhs.get_scalar();
2623 
2624  return op_for_non_nan(fp_lhs, fp_rhs);
2625 }
2626 
2627 // Handle execution based on instruction types.
2628 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp6() {
2629  int64_t alu_out;
2630  // Next pc.
2631  int64_t next_pc = bad_ra;
2632 
2633  // Branch instructions common part.
2634  auto BranchAndLinkHelper = [this, &next_pc]() {
2635  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2636  set_register(ra, current_pc + kInstrSize);
2637  int32_t offs26_low16 =
2638  static_cast<uint32_t>(instr_.Bits(25, 10) << 16) >> 16;
2639  int32_t offs26_high10 = static_cast<int32_t>(instr_.Bits(9, 0) << 22) >> 6;
2640  int32_t offs26 = offs26_low16 | offs26_high10;
2641  next_pc = current_pc + (offs26 << 2);
2642  printf_instr("Offs26: %08x\n", offs26);
2643  set_pc(next_pc);
2644  };
2645 
2646  auto BranchOff16Helper = [this, &next_pc](bool do_branch) {
2647  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2648  int32_t offs16 = static_cast<int32_t>(instr_.Bits(25, 10) << 16) >> 16;
2649  printf_instr("Offs16: %08x\n", offs16);
2650  int32_t offs = do_branch ? (offs16 << 2) : kInstrSize;
2651  next_pc = current_pc + offs;
2652  set_pc(next_pc);
2653  };
2654 
2655  auto BranchOff21Helper = [this, &next_pc](bool do_branch) {
2656  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2657  int32_t offs21_low16 =
2658  static_cast<uint32_t>(instr_.Bits(25, 10) << 16) >> 16;
2659  int32_t offs21_high5 = static_cast<int32_t>(instr_.Bits(4, 0) << 27) >> 11;
2660  int32_t offs = offs21_low16 | offs21_high5;
2661  printf_instr("Offs21: %08x\n", offs);
2662  offs = do_branch ? (offs << 2) : kInstrSize;
2663  next_pc = current_pc + offs;
2664  set_pc(next_pc);
2665  };
2666 
2667  auto BranchOff26Helper = [this, &next_pc]() {
2668  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2669  int32_t offs26_low16 =
2670  static_cast<uint32_t>(instr_.Bits(25, 10) << 16) >> 16;
2671  int32_t offs26_high10 = static_cast<int32_t>(instr_.Bits(9, 0) << 22) >> 6;
2672  int32_t offs26 = offs26_low16 | offs26_high10;
2673  next_pc = current_pc + (offs26 << 2);
2674  printf_instr("Offs26: %08x\n", offs26);
2675  set_pc(next_pc);
2676  };
2677 
2678  auto JumpOff16Helper = [this, &next_pc]() {
2679  int32_t offs16 = static_cast<int32_t>(instr_.Bits(25, 10) << 16) >> 16;
2680  printf_instr("JIRL\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, offs16: %x\n",
2681  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2682  rj(), offs16);
2683  set_register(rd_reg(), get_pc() + kInstrSize);
2684  next_pc = rj() + (offs16 << 2);
2685  set_pc(next_pc);
2686  };
2687 
2688  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 26) << 26) {
2689  case ADDU16I_D: {
2690  printf_instr("ADDU16I_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si16: %d\n",
2691  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2692  rj(), si16());
2693  int32_t si16_upper = static_cast<int32_t>(si16()) << 16;
2694  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(si16_upper) + rj();
2695  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2696  break;
2697  }
2698  case BEQZ:
2699  printf_instr("BEQZ\t %s: %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj());
2700  BranchOff21Helper(rj() == 0);
2701  break;
2702  case BNEZ:
2703  printf_instr("BNEZ\t %s: %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj());
2704  BranchOff21Helper(rj() != 0);
2705  break;
2706  case BCZ: {
2707  if (instr_.Bits(9, 8) == 0b00) {
2708  // BCEQZ
2709  printf_instr("BCEQZ\t fcc%d: %s, ", cj_reg(), cj() ? "True" : "False");
2710  BranchOff21Helper(cj() == false);
2711  } else if (instr_.Bits(9, 8) == 0b01) {
2712  // BCNEZ
2713  printf_instr("BCNEZ\t fcc%d: %s, ", cj_reg(), cj() ? "True" : "False");
2714  BranchOff21Helper(cj() == true);
2715  } else {
2716  UNREACHABLE();
2717  }
2718  break;
2719  }
2720  case JIRL:
2721  JumpOff16Helper();
2722  break;
2723  case B:
2724  printf_instr("B\t ");
2725  BranchOff26Helper();
2726  break;
2727  case BL:
2728  printf_instr("BL\t ");
2729  BranchAndLinkHelper();
2730  break;
2731  case BEQ:
2732  printf_instr("BEQ\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2733  rj(), Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd());
2734  BranchOff16Helper(rj() == rd());
2735  break;
2736  case BNE:
2737  printf_instr("BNE\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2738  rj(), Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd());
2739  BranchOff16Helper(rj() != rd());
2740  break;
2741  case BLT:
2742  printf_instr("BLT\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2743  rj(), Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd());
2744  BranchOff16Helper(rj() < rd());
2745  break;
2746  case BGE:
2747  printf_instr("BGE\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2748  rj(), Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd());
2749  BranchOff16Helper(rj() >= rd());
2750  break;
2751  case BLTU:
2752  printf_instr("BLTU\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2753  rj(), Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd());
2754  BranchOff16Helper(rj_u() < rd_u());
2755  break;
2756  case BGEU:
2757  printf_instr("BGEU\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, ", Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2758  rj(), Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd());
2759  BranchOff16Helper(rj_u() >= rd_u());
2760  break;
2761  default:
2762  UNREACHABLE();
2763  }
2764 }
2765 
2766 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp7() {
2767  int64_t alu_out;
2768 
2769  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 25) << 25) {
2770  case LU12I_W: {
2771  printf_instr("LU12I_W\t %s: %016lx, si20: %d\n",
2772  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), si20());
2773  int32_t si20_upper = static_cast<int32_t>(si20() << 12);
2774  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(si20_upper));
2775  break;
2776  }
2777  case LU32I_D: {
2778  printf_instr("LU32I_D\t %s: %016lx, si20: %d\n",
2779  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), si20());
2780  int32_t si20_signExtend = static_cast<int32_t>(si20() << 12) >> 12;
2781  int64_t lower_32bit_mask = 0xFFFFFFFF;
2782  alu_out = (static_cast<int64_t>(si20_signExtend) << 32) |
2783  (rd() & lower_32bit_mask);
2784  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2785  break;
2786  }
2787  case PCADDI: {
2788  printf_instr("PCADDI\t %s: %016lx, si20: %d\n", Registers::Name(rd_reg()),
2789  rd(), si20());
2790  int32_t si20_signExtend = static_cast<int32_t>(si20() << 12) >> 10;
2791  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2792  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(si20_signExtend) + current_pc;
2793  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2794  break;
2795  }
2796  case PCALAU12I: {
2797  printf_instr("PCALAU12I\t %s: %016lx, si20: %d\n",
2798  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), si20());
2799  int32_t si20_signExtend = static_cast<int32_t>(si20() << 12);
2800  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2801  int64_t clear_lower12bit_mask = 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFF000;
2802  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(si20_signExtend) + current_pc;
2803  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out & clear_lower12bit_mask);
2804  break;
2805  }
2806  case PCADDU12I: {
2807  printf_instr("PCADDU12I\t %s: %016lx, si20: %d\n",
2808  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), si20());
2809  int32_t si20_signExtend = static_cast<int32_t>(si20() << 12);
2810  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2811  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(si20_signExtend) + current_pc;
2812  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2813  break;
2814  }
2815  case PCADDU18I: {
2816  printf_instr("PCADDU18I\t %s: %016lx, si20: %d\n",
2817  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), si20());
2818  int64_t si20_signExtend = (static_cast<int64_t>(si20()) << 44) >> 26;
2819  int64_t current_pc = get_pc();
2820  alu_out = si20_signExtend + current_pc;
2821  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2822  break;
2823  }
2824  default:
2825  UNREACHABLE();
2826  }
2827 }
2828 
2829 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp8() {
2830  int64_t addr = 0x0;
2831  int64_t si14_se = (static_cast<int64_t>(si14()) << 50) >> 48;
2832 
2833  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 24) << 24) {
2834  case LDPTR_W:
2835  printf_instr("LDPTR_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2836  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2837  rj(), si14_se);
2838  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si14_se, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
2839  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadW(rj() + si14_se, instr_.instr()));
2840  break;
2841  case STPTR_W:
2842  printf_instr("STPTR_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2843  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2844  rj(), si14_se);
2845  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si14_se, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
2846  WriteW(rj() + si14_se, static_cast<int32_t>(rd()), instr_.instr());
2847  break;
2848  case LDPTR_D:
2849  printf_instr("LDPTR_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2850  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2851  rj(), si14_se);
2852  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si14_se, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
2853  set_register(rd_reg(), Read2W(rj() + si14_se, instr_.instr()));
2854  break;
2855  case STPTR_D:
2856  printf_instr("STPTR_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2857  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2858  rj(), si14_se);
2859  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si14_se, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
2860  Write2W(rj() + si14_se, rd(), instr_.instr());
2861  break;
2862  case LL_W: {
2863  printf_instr("LL_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2864  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2865  rj(), si14_se);
2866  addr = si14_se + rj();
2867  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
2868  {
2869  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&GlobalMonitor::Get()->mutex);
2870  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadW(addr, instr_.instr()));
2871  local_monitor_.NotifyLoadLinked(addr, TransactionSize::Word);
2872  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(addr,
2873  &global_monitor_thread_);
2874  }
2875  break;
2876  }
2877  case SC_W: {
2878  printf_instr("SC_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2879  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2880  rj(), si14_se);
2881  addr = si14_se + rj();
2882  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
2883  int32_t LLbit = 0;
2884  WriteConditionalW(addr, static_cast<int32_t>(rd()), instr_.instr(),
2885  &LLbit);
2886  set_register(rd_reg(), LLbit);
2887  break;
2888  }
2889  case LL_D: {
2890  printf_instr("LL_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2891  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2892  rj(), si14_se);
2893  addr = si14_se + rj();
2894  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
2895  {
2896  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&GlobalMonitor::Get()->mutex);
2897  set_register(rd_reg(), Read2W(addr, instr_.instr()));
2898  local_monitor_.NotifyLoadLinked(addr, TransactionSize::DoubleWord);
2899  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(addr,
2900  &global_monitor_thread_);
2901  }
2902  break;
2903  }
2904  case SC_D: {
2905  printf_instr("SC_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si14: %016lx\n",
2906  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2907  rj(), si14_se);
2908  addr = si14_se + rj();
2909  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
2910  int32_t LLbit = 0;
2911  WriteConditional2W(addr, rd(), instr_.instr(), &LLbit);
2912  set_register(rd_reg(), LLbit);
2913  break;
2914  }
2915  default:
2916  UNREACHABLE();
2917  }
2918 }
2919 
2920 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp10() {
2921  int64_t alu_out = 0x0;
2922  int64_t si12_se = (static_cast<int64_t>(si12()) << 52) >> 52;
2923  uint64_t si12_ze = (static_cast<uint64_t>(ui12()) << 52) >> 52;
2924 
2925  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 22) << 22) {
2926  case BSTR_W: {
2927  CHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(21), 1);
2928  uint8_t lsbw_ = lsbw();
2929  uint8_t msbw_ = msbw();
2930  CHECK_LE(lsbw_, msbw_);
2931  uint8_t size = msbw_ - lsbw_ + 1;
2932  uint64_t mask = (1ULL << size) - 1;
2933  if (instr_.Bit(15) == 0) {
2934  // BSTRINS_W
2935  printf_instr(
2936  "BSTRINS_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, msbw: %02x, lsbw: %02x\n",
2937  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(),
2938  msbw_, lsbw_);
2939  alu_out = static_cast<int32_t>((rd_u() & ~(mask << lsbw_)) |
2940  ((rj_u() & mask) << lsbw_));
2941  } else {
2942  // BSTRPICK_W
2943  printf_instr(
2944  "BSTRPICK_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, msbw: %02x, lsbw: %02x\n",
2945  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(),
2946  msbw_, lsbw_);
2947  alu_out = static_cast<int32_t>((rj_u() & (mask << lsbw_)) >> lsbw_);
2948  }
2949  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2950  break;
2951  }
2952  case BSTRINS_D: {
2953  uint8_t lsbd_ = lsbd();
2954  uint8_t msbd_ = msbd();
2955  CHECK_LE(lsbd_, msbd_);
2956  printf_instr(
2957  "BSTRINS_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, msbw: %02x, lsbw: %02x\n",
2958  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(),
2959  msbd_, lsbd_);
2960  uint8_t size = msbd_ - lsbd_ + 1;
2961  if (size < 64) {
2962  uint64_t mask = (1ULL << size) - 1;
2963  alu_out = (rd_u() & ~(mask << lsbd_)) | ((rj_u() & mask) << lsbd_);
2964  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2965  } else if (size == 64) {
2966  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj());
2967  }
2968  break;
2969  }
2970  case BSTRPICK_D: {
2971  uint8_t lsbd_ = lsbd();
2972  uint8_t msbd_ = msbd();
2973  CHECK_LE(lsbd_, msbd_);
2974  printf_instr(
2975  "BSTRPICK_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, msbw: %02x, lsbw: %02x\n",
2976  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(),
2977  msbd_, lsbd_);
2978  uint8_t size = msbd_ - lsbd_ + 1;
2979  if (size < 64) {
2980  uint64_t mask = (1ULL << size) - 1;
2981  alu_out = (rj_u() & (mask << lsbd_)) >> lsbd_;
2982  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
2983  } else if (size == 64) {
2984  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj());
2985  }
2986  break;
2987  }
2988  case SLTI:
2989  printf_instr("SLTI\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
2990  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2991  rj(), si12_se);
2992  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj() < si12_se ? 1 : 0);
2993  break;
2994  case SLTUI:
2995  printf_instr("SLTUI\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
2996  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
2997  rj(), si12_se);
2998  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj_u() < static_cast<uint64_t>(si12_se) ? 1 : 0);
2999  break;
3000  case ADDI_W: {
3001  printf_instr("ADDI_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3002  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3003  rj(), si12_se);
3004  int32_t alu32_out =
3005  static_cast<int32_t>(rj()) + static_cast<int32_t>(si12_se);
3006  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu32_out);
3007  break;
3008  }
3009  case ADDI_D:
3010  printf_instr("ADDI_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3011  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3012  rj(), si12_se);
3013  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj() + si12_se);
3014  break;
3015  case LU52I_D: {
3016  printf_instr("LU52I_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3017  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3018  rj(), si12_se);
3019  int64_t si12_se = static_cast<int64_t>(si12()) << 52;
3020  uint64_t mask = (1ULL << 52) - 1;
3021  alu_out = si12_se + (rj() & mask);
3022  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
3023  break;
3024  }
3025  case ANDI:
3026  printf_instr("ANDI\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3027  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3028  rj(), si12_ze);
3029  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj() & si12_ze);
3030  break;
3031  case ORI:
3032  printf_instr("ORI\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3033  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3034  rj(), si12_ze);
3035  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj_u() | si12_ze);
3036  break;
3037  case XORI:
3038  printf_instr("XORI\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3039  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3040  rj(), si12_ze);
3041  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj_u() ^ si12_ze);
3042  break;
3043  case LD_B:
3044  printf_instr("LD_B\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3045  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3046  rj(), si12_ze);
3047  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int8_t))) return;
3048  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadB(rj() + si12_se));
3049  break;
3050  case LD_H:
3051  printf_instr("LD_H\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3052  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3053  rj(), si12_ze);
3054  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int16_t))) return;
3055  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadH(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr()));
3056  break;
3057  case LD_W:
3058  printf_instr("LD_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3059  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3060  rj(), si12_ze);
3061  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
3062  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadW(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr()));
3063  break;
3064  case LD_D:
3065  printf_instr("LD_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3066  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3067  rj(), si12_ze);
3068  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
3069  set_register(rd_reg(), Read2W(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr()));
3070  break;
3071  case ST_B:
3072  printf_instr("ST_B\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3073  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3074  rj(), si12_ze);
3075  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int8_t))) return;
3076  WriteB(rj() + si12_se, static_cast<int8_t>(rd()));
3077  break;
3078  case ST_H:
3079  printf_instr("ST_H\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3080  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3081  rj(), si12_ze);
3082  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int16_t))) return;
3083  WriteH(rj() + si12_se, static_cast<int16_t>(rd()), instr_.instr());
3084  break;
3085  case ST_W:
3086  printf_instr("ST_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3087  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3088  rj(), si12_ze);
3089  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
3090  WriteW(rj() + si12_se, static_cast<int32_t>(rd()), instr_.instr());
3091  break;
3092  case ST_D:
3093  printf_instr("ST_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3094  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3095  rj(), si12_ze);
3096  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
3097  Write2W(rj() + si12_se, rd(), instr_.instr());
3098  break;
3099  case LD_BU:
3100  printf_instr("LD_BU\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3101  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3102  rj(), si12_ze);
3103  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(uint8_t))) return;
3104  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadBU(rj() + si12_se));
3105  break;
3106  case LD_HU:
3107  printf_instr("LD_HU\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3108  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3109  rj(), si12_ze);
3110  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(uint16_t))) return;
3111  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadHU(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr()));
3112  break;
3113  case LD_WU:
3114  printf_instr("LD_WU\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3115  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3116  rj(), si12_ze);
3117  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(uint32_t))) return;
3118  set_register(rd_reg(), ReadWU(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr()));
3119  break;
3120  case FLD_S: {
3121  printf_instr("FLD_S\t %s: %016f, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3122  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_float(),
3123  Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(), si12_ze);
3124  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(float))) return;
3125  set_fpu_register(fd_reg(), kFPUInvalidResult); // Trash upper 32 bits.
3126  set_fpu_register_word(
3127  fd_reg(), ReadW(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr(), FLOAT_DOUBLE));
3128  break;
3129  }
3130  case FST_S: {
3131  printf_instr("FST_S\t %s: %016f, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3132  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_float(),
3133  Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(), si12_ze);
3134  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(float))) return;
3135  int32_t alu_out_32 = static_cast<int32_t>(get_fpu_register(fd_reg()));
3136  WriteW(rj() + si12_se, alu_out_32, instr_.instr());
3137  break;
3138  }
3139  case FLD_D: {
3140  printf_instr("FLD_D\t %s: %016f, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3141  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_double(),
3142  Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(), si12_ze);
3143  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(double))) return;
3144  set_fpu_register_double(fd_reg(), ReadD(rj() + si12_se, instr_.instr()));
3145  TraceMemRd(rj() + si12_se, get_fpu_register(fd_reg()), DOUBLE);
3146  break;
3147  }
3148  case FST_D: {
3149  printf_instr("FST_D\t %s: %016f, %s: %016lx, si12: %016lx\n",
3150  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_double(),
3151  Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj(), si12_ze);
3152  if (!ProbeMemory(rj() + si12_se, sizeof(double))) return;
3153  WriteD(rj() + si12_se, get_fpu_register_double(fd_reg()), instr_.instr());
3154  TraceMemWr(rj() + si12_se, get_fpu_register(fd_reg()), DWORD);
3155  break;
3156  }
3157  default:
3158  UNREACHABLE();
3159  }
3160 }
3161 
3162 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp12() {
3163  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 20) << 20) {
3164  case FMADD_S:

3321  case SEQ:

3454 
3455 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp14() {
3456  int64_t alu_out = 0x0;
3457  int32_t alu32_out = 0x0;
3458 
3459  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 18) << 18) {
3460  case ALSL: {
3461  uint8_t sa = sa2() + 1;
3462  alu32_out =
3463  (static_cast<int32_t>(rj()) << sa) + static_cast<int32_t>(rk());
3464  if (instr_.Bit(17) == 0) {
3465  // ALSL_W
3466  printf_instr("ALSL_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, sa2: %d\n",
3467  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3468  rj(), Registers::Name(rk_reg()), rk(), sa2());
3469  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu32_out);
3470  } else {
3471  // ALSL_WU
3472  printf_instr("ALSL_WU\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, sa2: %d\n",
3473  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3474  rj(), Registers::Name(rk_reg()), rk(), sa2());
3475  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<uint32_t>(alu32_out));
3476  }
3477  break;
3478  }
3479  case BYTEPICK_W: {
3480  CHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(17), 0);
3481  printf_instr("BYTEPICK_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, sa2: %d\n",
3482  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3483  rj(), Registers::Name(rk_reg()), rk(), sa2());
3484  uint8_t sa = sa2() * 8;
3485  if (sa == 0) {
3486  alu32_out = static_cast<int32_t>(rk());
3487  } else {
3488  int32_t mask = (1 << 31) >> (sa - 1);
3489  int32_t rk_hi = (static_cast<int32_t>(rk()) & (~mask)) << sa;
3490  int32_t rj_lo = (static_cast<uint32_t>(rj()) & mask) >> (32 - sa);
3491  alu32_out = rk_hi | rj_lo;
3492  }
3493  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(alu32_out));
3494  break;
3495  }
3496  case BYTEPICK_D: {
3497  printf_instr("BYTEPICK_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, sa3: %d\n",
3498  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3499  rj(), Registers::Name(rk_reg()), rk(), sa3());
3500  uint8_t sa = sa3() * 8;
3501  if (sa == 0) {
3502  alu_out = rk();
3503  } else {
3504  int64_t mask = (1LL << 63) >> (sa - 1);
3505  int64_t rk_hi = (rk() & (~mask)) << sa;
3506  int64_t rj_lo = static_cast<uint64_t>(rj() & mask) >> (64 - sa);
3507  alu_out = rk_hi | rj_lo;
3508  }
3509  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
3510  break;
3511  }
3512  case ALSL_D: {
3513  printf_instr("ALSL_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, sa2: %d\n",
3514  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3515  rj(), Registers::Name(rk_reg()), rk(), sa2());
3516  CHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(17), 0);
3517  uint8_t sa = sa2() + 1;
3518  alu_out = (rj() << sa) + rk();
3519  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
3520  break;
3521  }
3522  case SLLI: {
3523  DCHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(17), 0);
3524  if (instr_.Bits(17, 15) == 0b001) {
3525  // SLLI_W
3526  printf_instr("SLLI_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui5: %d\n",
3527  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3528  rj(), ui5());
3529  alu32_out = static_cast<int32_t>(rj()) << ui5();
3530  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(alu32_out));
3531  } else if ((instr_.Bits(17, 16) == 0b01)) {
3532  // SLLI_D
3533  printf_instr("SLLI_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui6: %d\n",
3534  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3535  rj(), ui6());
3536  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj() << ui6());
3537  }
3538  break;
3539  }
3540  case SRLI: {
3541  DCHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(17), 0);
3542  if (instr_.Bits(17, 15) == 0b001) {
3543  // SRLI_W
3544  printf_instr("SRLI_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui5: %d\n",
3545  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3546  rj(), ui5());
3547  alu32_out = static_cast<uint32_t>(rj()) >> ui5();
3548  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(alu32_out));
3549  } else if (instr_.Bits(17, 16) == 0b01) {
3550  // SRLI_D
3551  printf_instr("SRLI_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui6: %d\n",
3552  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3553  rj(), ui6());
3554  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj_u() >> ui6());
3555  }
3556  break;
3557  }
3558  case SRAI: {
3559  DCHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(17), 0);
3560  if (instr_.Bits(17, 15) == 0b001) {
3561  // SRAI_W
3562  printf_instr("SRAI_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui5: %d\n",
3563  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3564  rj(), ui5());
3565  alu32_out = static_cast<int32_t>(rj()) >> ui5();
3566  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(alu32_out));
3567  } else if (instr_.Bits(17, 16) == 0b01) {
3568  // SRAI_D
3569  printf_instr("SRAI_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui6: %d\n",
3570  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3571  rj(), ui6());
3572  SetResult(rd_reg(), rj() >> ui6());
3573  }
3574  break;
3575  }
3576  case ROTRI: {
3577  DCHECK_EQ(instr_.Bit(17), 0);
3578  if (instr_.Bits(17, 15) == 0b001) {
3579  // ROTRI_W
3580  printf_instr("ROTRI_W\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui5: %d\n",
3581  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3582  rj(), ui5());
3583  alu32_out = static_cast<int32_t>(
3584  base::bits::RotateRight32(static_cast<const uint32_t>(rj_u()),
3585  static_cast<const uint32_t>(ui5())));
3586  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(alu32_out));
3587  } else if (instr_.Bits(17, 16) == 0b01) {
3588  // ROTRI_D
3589  printf_instr("ROTRI_D\t %s: %016lx, %s: %016lx, ui6: %d\n",
3590  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3591  rj(), ui6());
3592  alu_out =
3593  static_cast<int64_t>(base::bits::RotateRight64(rj_u(), ui6()));
3594  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
3595  printf_instr("ROTRI, %s, %s, %d\n", Registers::Name(rd_reg()),
3596  Registers::Name(rj_reg()), ui6());
3597  }
3598  break;
3599  }
3600  default:
3601  UNREACHABLE();
3602  }
3603 }
3604 
3605 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp17() {
3606  int64_t alu_out;
3607 
3608  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 15) << 15) {
3609  case ADD_W: {
3610  printf_instr("ADD_W\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
3611  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
3612  rj(), Registers::Name(rk_reg()), rk());
3613  int32_t alu32_out = static_cast<int32_t>(rj() + rk());
3614  // Sign-extend result of 32bit operation into 64bit register.
3615  SetResult(rd_reg(), static_cast<int64_t>(alu32_out));
3616  break;
3617  }
3618  case ADD_D:
3619  printf_instr("ADD_D\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
3620  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),

4487  SetFPUDoubleResult(fd_reg(), std::copysign(fj_double(), fk_double()));
4488  } break;
4489  default:
4490  UNREACHABLE();
4491  }
4492 }
4493 
4494 void Simulator::DecodeTypeOp22() {
4495  int64_t alu_out;
4496 
4497  switch (instr_.Bits(31, 10) << 10) {
4498  case CLZ_W: {
4499  printf_instr("CLZ_W\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4500  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4501  rj());
4502  alu_out = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(static_cast<int32_t>(rj_u()));
4503  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4504  break;
4505  }
4506  case CTZ_W: {
4507  printf_instr("CTZ_W\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4508  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4509  rj());
4510  alu_out = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(static_cast<int32_t>(rj_u()));
4511  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4512  break;
4513  }
4514  case CLZ_D: {
4515  printf_instr("CLZ_D\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4516  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4517  rj());
4518  alu_out = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(static_cast<int64_t>(rj_u()));
4519  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4520  break;
4521  }
4522  case CTZ_D: {
4523  printf_instr("CTZ_D\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4524  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4525  rj());
4526  alu_out = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros64(static_cast<int64_t>(rj_u()));
4527  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4528  break;
4529  }
4530  case REVB_2H: {
4531  printf_instr("REVB_2H\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4532  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4533  rj());
4534  uint32_t input = static_cast<uint32_t>(rj());
4535  uint64_t output = 0;
4536 
4537  uint32_t mask = 0xFF000000;
4538  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4539  uint32_t tmp = mask & input;
4540  if (i % 2 == 0) {
4541  tmp = tmp >> 8;
4542  } else {
4543  tmp = tmp << 8;
4544  }
4545  output = output | tmp;
4546  mask = mask >> 8;
4547  }
4548 
4549  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<int32_t>(output));
4550  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4551  break;
4552  }
4553  case REVB_4H: {
4554  printf_instr("REVB_4H\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4555  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4556  rj());
4557  uint64_t input = rj_u();
4558  uint64_t output = 0;
4559 
4560  uint64_t mask = 0xFF00000000000000;
4561  for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
4562  uint64_t tmp = mask & input;
4563  if (i % 2 == 0) {
4564  tmp = tmp >> 8;
4565  } else {
4566  tmp = tmp << 8;
4567  }
4568  output = output | tmp;
4569  mask = mask >> 8;
4570  }
4571 
4572  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(output);
4573  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4574  break;
4575  }
4576  case REVB_2W: {
4577  printf_instr("REVB_2W\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4578  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4579  rj());
4580  uint64_t input = rj_u();
4581  uint64_t output = 0;
4582 
4583  uint64_t mask = 0xFF000000FF000000;
4584  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4585  uint64_t tmp = mask & input;
4586  if (i <= 1) {
4587  tmp = tmp >> (24 - i * 16);
4588  } else {
4589  tmp = tmp << (i * 16 - 24);
4590  }
4591  output = output | tmp;
4592  mask = mask >> 8;
4593  }
4594 
4595  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(output);
4596  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4597  break;
4598  }
4599  case REVB_D: {
4600  printf_instr("REVB_D\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4601  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4602  rj());
4603  uint64_t input = rj_u();
4604  uint64_t output = 0;
4605 
4606  uint64_t mask = 0xFF00000000000000;
4607  for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
4608  uint64_t tmp = mask & input;
4609  if (i <= 3) {
4610  tmp = tmp >> (56 - i * 16);
4611  } else {
4612  tmp = tmp << (i * 16 - 56);
4613  }
4614  output = output | tmp;
4615  mask = mask >> 8;
4616  }
4617 
4618  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(output);
4619  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4620  break;
4621  }
4622  case REVH_2W: {
4623  printf_instr("REVH_2W\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4624  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4625  rj());
4626  uint64_t input = rj_u();
4627  uint64_t output = 0;
4628 
4629  uint64_t mask = 0xFFFF000000000000;
4630  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4631  uint64_t tmp = mask & input;
4632  if (i % 2 == 0) {
4633  tmp = tmp >> 16;
4634  } else {
4635  tmp = tmp << 16;
4636  }
4637  output = output | tmp;
4638  mask = mask >> 16;
4639  }
4640 
4641  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(output);
4642  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4643  break;
4644  }
4645  case REVH_D: {
4646  printf_instr("REVH_D\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4647  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4648  rj());
4649  uint64_t input = rj_u();
4650  uint64_t output = 0;
4651 
4652  uint64_t mask = 0xFFFF000000000000;
4653  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4654  uint64_t tmp = mask & input;
4655  if (i <= 1) {
4656  tmp = tmp >> (48 - i * 32);
4657  } else {
4658  tmp = tmp << (i * 32 - 48);
4659  }
4660  output = output | tmp;
4661  mask = mask >> 16;
4662  }
4663 
4664  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(output);
4665  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4666  break;
4667  }
4668  case BITREV_4B: {
4669  printf_instr("BITREV_4B\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4670  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4671  rj());
4672  uint32_t input = static_cast<uint32_t>(rj());
4673  uint32_t output = 0;
4674  uint8_t i_byte, o_byte;
4675 
4676  // Reverse the bit in byte for each individual byte
4677  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4678  output = output >> 8;
4679  i_byte = input & 0xFF;
4680 
4681  // Fast way to reverse bits in byte
4682  // Devised by Sean Anderson, July 13, 2001
4683  o_byte = static_cast<uint8_t>(((i_byte * 0x0802LU & 0x22110LU) |
4684  (i_byte * 0x8020LU & 0x88440LU)) *
4685  0x10101LU >>
4686  16);
4687 
4688  output = output | (static_cast<uint32_t>(o_byte << 24));
4689  input = input >> 8;
4690  }
4691 
4692  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<int32_t>(output));
4693  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4694  break;
4695  }
4696  case BITREV_8B: {
4697  printf_instr("BITREV_8B\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4698  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4699  rj());
4700  uint64_t input = rj_u();
4701  uint64_t output = 0;
4702  uint8_t i_byte, o_byte;
4703 
4704  // Reverse the bit in byte for each individual byte
4705  for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
4706  output = output >> 8;
4707  i_byte = input & 0xFF;
4708 
4709  // Fast way to reverse bits in byte
4710  // Devised by Sean Anderson, July 13, 2001
4711  o_byte = static_cast<uint8_t>(((i_byte * 0x0802LU & 0x22110LU) |
4712  (i_byte * 0x8020LU & 0x88440LU)) *
4713  0x10101LU >>
4714  16);
4715 
4716  output = output | (static_cast<uint64_t>(o_byte) << 56);
4717  input = input >> 8;
4718  }
4719 
4720  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(output);
4721  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4722  break;
4723  }
4724  case BITREV_W: {
4725  printf_instr("BITREV_W\t %s: %016lx, %s, %016lx\n",
4726  Registers::Name(rd_reg()), rd(), Registers::Name(rj_reg()),
4727  rj());
4728  uint32_t input = static_cast<uint32_t>(rj());
4729  uint32_t output = 0;
4730  output = base::bits::ReverseBits(input);
4731  alu_out = static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<int32_t>(output));
4732  SetResult(rd_reg(), alu_out);
4733  break;

4990  double fj = fj_double();
4991  double rounded = ceil(fj);
4992  int64_t result = static_cast<int64_t>(rounded);
4993  SetFPUResult(fd_reg(), result);
4994  if (set_fcsr_round64_error(fj, rounded)) {
4995  set_fpu_register_invalid_result64(fj, rounded);
4996  }
4997  break;
4998  }
4999  case FTINTRZ_W_S: {
5000  printf_instr("FTINTRZ_W_S\t %s: %016f, %s, %016f\n",
5001  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_double(),
5002  FPURegisters::Name(fj_reg()), fj_float());
5003  float fj = fj_float();
5004  float rounded = trunc(fj);
5005  int32_t result = static_cast<int32_t>(rounded);
5006  SetFPUWordResult(fd_reg(), result);
5007  if (set_fcsr_round_error(fj, rounded)) {
5008  set_fpu_register_word_invalid_result(fj, rounded);
5009  }
5010  break;

5200  SetFPUDoubleResult(fd_reg(), static_cast<double>(alu_out));
5201  break;
5202  }
5203  case FFINT_D_L: {
5204  alu_out = get_fpu_register(fj_reg());
5205  printf_instr("FFINT_D_L\t %s: %016f, %s, %016lx\n",
5206  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_double(),
5207  FPURegisters::Name(fj_reg()), alu_out);
5208  SetFPUDoubleResult(fd_reg(), static_cast<double>(alu_out));
5209  break;
5210  }
5211  case FRINT_S: {
5212  printf_instr("FRINT_S\t %s: %016f, %s, %016f mode : ",
5213  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_float(),
5214  FPURegisters::Name(fj_reg()), fj_float());
5215  float fj = fj_float();
5216  float result, temp_result;
5217  double temp;
5218  float upper = ceil(fj);
5219  float lower = floor(fj);
5220  switch (get_fcsr_rounding_mode()) {
5221  case kRoundToNearest:
5222  printf_instr(" kRoundToNearest\n");
5223  if (upper - fj < fj - lower) {
5224  result = upper;
5225  } else if (upper - fj > fj - lower) {
5226  result = lower;
5227  } else {
5228  temp_result = upper / 2;
5229  float reminder = std::modf(temp_result, &temp);
5230  if (reminder == 0) {
5231  result = upper;
5232  } else {
5233  result = lower;
5234  }
5235  }
5236  break;
5237  case kRoundToZero:
5238  printf_instr(" kRoundToZero\n");
5239  result = (fj > 0 ? lower : upper);
5240  break;
5241  case kRoundToPlusInf:
5242  printf_instr(" kRoundToPlusInf\n");
5243  result = upper;
5244  break;
5245  case kRoundToMinusInf:
5246  printf_instr(" kRoundToMinusInf\n");
5247  result = lower;
5248  break;
5249  }
5250  SetFPUFloatResult(fd_reg(), result);
5251  set_fcsr_bit(kFCSRInexactCauseBit, result != fj);
5252  break;
5253  }
5254  case FRINT_D: {
5255  printf_instr("FRINT_D\t %s: %016f, %s, %016f mode : ",
5256  FPURegisters::Name(fd_reg()), fd_double(),
5257  FPURegisters::Name(fj_reg()), fj_double());
5258  double fj = fj_double();
5259  double result, temp, temp_result;
5260  double upper = ceil(fj);
5261  double lower = floor(fj);
5262  switch (get_fcsr_rounding_mode()) {
5263  case kRoundToNearest:
5264  printf_instr(" kRoundToNearest\n");
5265  if (upper - fj < fj - lower) {
5266  result = upper;
5267  } else if (upper - fj > fj - lower) {
5268  result = lower;
5269  } else {
5270  temp_result = upper / 2;
5271  double reminder = std::modf(temp_result, &temp);
5272  if (reminder == 0) {
5273  result = upper;
5274  } else {
5275  result = lower;
5276  }
5277  }
5278  break;
5279  case kRoundToZero:
5280  printf_instr(" kRoundToZero\n");
5281  result = (fj > 0 ? lower : upper);
5282  break;
5283  case kRoundToPlusInf:
5284  printf_instr(" kRoundToPlusInf\n");
5285  result = upper;
5286  break;
5287  case kRoundToMinusInf:
5288  printf_instr(" kRoundToMinusInf\n");
5289  result = lower;
5290  break;
5291  }
5292  SetFPUDoubleResult(fd_reg(), result);
5293  set_fcsr_bit(kFCSRInexactCauseBit, result != fj);
5294  break;
5295  }
5296  case MOVFR2CF:
5297  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: MOVFR2CF\n");
5298  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5299  case MOVCF2FR:
5300  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: MOVCF2FR\n");
5301  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5302  case MOVGR2CF:
5303  printf_instr("MOVGR2CF\t FCC%d, %s: %016lx\n", cd_reg(),
5304  Registers::Name(rj_reg()), rj());
5305  set_cf_register(cd_reg(), rj() & 1);
5306  break;
5307  case MOVCF2GR:
5308  printf_instr("MOVCF2GR\t %s: %016lx, FCC%d\n", Registers::Name(rd_reg()),
5309  rd(), cj_reg());
5310  SetResult(rd_reg(), cj());
5311  break;
5312  case FRECIP_S:
5313  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FRECIP_S\n");
5314  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5315  case FRECIP_D:
5316  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FRECIP_D\n");
5317  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5318  case FRSQRT_S:
5319  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FRSQRT_S\n");
5320  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5321  case FRSQRT_D:
5322  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FRSQRT_D\n");
5323  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5324  case FCLASS_S:
5325  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FCLASS_S\n");
5326  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5327  case FCLASS_D:
5328  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FCLASS_D\n");
5329  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5330  case FLOGB_S:
5331  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FLOGB_S\n");
5332  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5333  case FLOGB_D:
5334  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: FLOGB_D\n");

5340  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: CTO_W\n");

5342  case CLO_D:
5343  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: CLO_D\n");
5344  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5345  case CTO_D:
5346  printf("Sim UNIMPLEMENTED: CTO_D\n");
5347  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5348  // Unimplemented opcodes raised an error in the configuration step before,
5349  // so we can use the default here to set the destination register in common
5350  // cases.
5351  default:
5352  UNREACHABLE();
5353  }

5355 
5356 // Executes the current instruction.
5357 void Simulator::InstructionDecode(Instruction* instr) {
5358  if (v8_flags.check_icache) {
5359  CheckICache(i_cache(), instr);
5360  }
5361  pc_modified_ = false;
5362 
5363  v8::base::EmbeddedVector<char, 256> buffer;
5364 
5365  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
5366  base::SNPrintF(trace_buf_, " ");
5367  disasm::NameConverter converter;
5368  disasm::Disassembler dasm(converter);
5369  // Use a reasonably large buffer.
5370  dasm.InstructionDecode(buffer, reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(instr));
5371  }
5372 
5373  static int instr_count = 0;
5374  USE(instr_count);
5375  instr_ = instr;
5376  printf_instr("\nInstr%3d: %08x, PC: %016lx\t", instr_count++,
5377  instr_.Bits(31, 0), get_pc());
5378  switch (instr_.InstructionType()) {
5379  case Instruction::kOp6Type:
5380  DecodeTypeOp6();
5381  break;
5382  case Instruction::kOp7Type:
5383  DecodeTypeOp7();
5384  break;
5385  case Instruction::kOp8Type:
5386  DecodeTypeOp8();
5387  break;
5388  case Instruction::kOp10Type:
5389  DecodeTypeOp10();
5390  break;
5391  case Instruction::kOp12Type:
5392  DecodeTypeOp12();
5393  break;
5394  case Instruction::kOp14Type:
5395  DecodeTypeOp14();
5396  break;
5397  case Instruction::kOp17Type:
5398  DecodeTypeOp17();
5399  break;
5400  case Instruction::kOp22Type:
5401  DecodeTypeOp22();
5402  break;
5403  default: {
5404  printf("instr_: %x\n", instr_.Bits(31, 0));
5405  UNREACHABLE();
5406  }
5407  }
5408 
5409  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
5410  PrintF(" 0x%08" PRIxPTR " %-44s %s\n",
5411  reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(instr), buffer.begin(),
5412  trace_buf_.begin());
5413  }
5414 
5415  if (!pc_modified_) {
5416  set_register(pc, reinterpret_cast<int64_t>(instr) + kInstrSize);
5417  }
5418 }
5419 
5420 void Simulator::Execute() {
5421  // Get the PC to simulate. Cannot use the accessor here as we need the
5422  // raw PC value and not the one used as input to arithmetic instructions.
5423  int64_t program_counter = get_pc();
5424  if (v8_flags.stop_sim_at == 0) {
5425  // Fast version of the dispatch loop without checking whether the simulator
5426  // should be stopping at a particular executed instruction.
5427  while (program_counter != end_sim_pc) {
5428  Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(program_counter);
5429  icount_++;
5430  InstructionDecode(instr);
5431  program_counter = get_pc();
5432  }
5433  } else {
5434  // v8_flags.stop_sim_at is at the non-default value. Stop in the debugger
5435  // when we reach the particular instruction count.
5436  while (program_counter != end_sim_pc) {
5437  Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(program_counter);
5438  icount_++;
5439  if (icount_ == static_cast<int64_t>(v8_flags.stop_sim_at)) {
5440  Loong64Debugger dbg(this);
5441  dbg.Debug();
5442  } else {
5443  InstructionDecode(instr);
5444  }
5445  program_counter = get_pc();
5446  }
5447  }
5448 }
5449 
5450 void Simulator::CallInternal(Address entry) {
5451  // Adjust JS-based stack limit to C-based stack limit.
5452  isolate_->stack_guard()->AdjustStackLimitForSimulator();
5453 
5454  // Prepare to execute the code at entry.
5455  set_register(pc, static_cast<int64_t>(entry));
5456  // Put down marker for end of simulation. The simulator will stop simulation
5457  // when the PC reaches this value. By saving the "end simulation" value into
5458  // the LR the simulation stops when returning to this call point.
5459  set_register(ra, end_sim_pc);
5460 
5461  // Remember the values of callee-saved registers.
5462  int64_t s0_val = get_register(s0);
5463  int64_t s1_val = get_register(s1);
5464  int64_t s2_val = get_register(s2);
5465  int64_t s3_val = get_register(s3);
5466  int64_t s4_val = get_register(s4);
5467  int64_t s5_val = get_register(s5);
5468  int64_t s6_val = get_register(s6);
5469  int64_t s7_val = get_register(s7);
5470  int64_t s8_val = get_register(s8);
5471  int64_t gp_val = get_register(gp);
5472  int64_t sp_val = get_register(sp);
5473  int64_t tp_val = get_register(tp);
5474  int64_t fp_val = get_register(fp);
5475 
5476  // Set up the callee-saved registers with a known value. To be able to check
5477  // that they are preserved properly across JS execution.
5478  int64_t callee_saved_value = icount_;
5479  set_register(s0, callee_saved_value);
5480  set_register(s1, callee_saved_value);
5481  set_register(s2, callee_saved_value);
5482  set_register(s3, callee_saved_value);
5483  set_register(s4, callee_saved_value);
5484  set_register(s5, callee_saved_value);
5485  set_register(s6, callee_saved_value);
5486  set_register(s7, callee_saved_value);
5487  set_register(s8, callee_saved_value);
5488  set_register(gp, callee_saved_value);
5489  set_register(tp, callee_saved_value);
5490  set_register(fp, callee_saved_value);
5491 
5492  // Start the simulation.
5493  Execute();
5494 
5495  // Check that the callee-saved registers have been preserved.
5496  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s0));
5497  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s1));
5498  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s2));
5499  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s3));
5500  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s4));
5501  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s5));
5502  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s6));
5503  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s7));
5504  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(s8));
5505  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(gp));
5506  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(tp));
5507  CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(fp));
5508 
5509  // Restore callee-saved registers with the original value.
5510  set_register(s0, s0_val);
5511  set_register(s1, s1_val);
5512  set_register(s2, s2_val);
5513  set_register(s3, s3_val);
5514  set_register(s4, s4_val);
5515  set_register(s5, s5_val);
5516  set_register(s6, s6_val);
5517  set_register(s7, s7_val);
5518  set_register(s8, s8_val);
5519  set_register(gp, gp_val);
5520  set_register(sp, sp_val);
5521  set_register(tp, tp_val);
5522  set_register(fp, fp_val);
5523 }
5524 
5525 void Simulator::CallImpl(Address entry, CallArgument* args) {
5526  int index_gp = 0;
5527  int index_fp = 0;
5528 
5529  std::vector<int64_t> stack_args(0);
5530  for (int i = 0; !args[i].IsEnd(); i++) {
5531  CallArgument arg = args[i];
5532  if (arg.IsGP() && (index_gp < 8)) {
5533  set_register(index_gp + 4, arg.bits());
5534  index_gp++;
5535  } else if (arg.IsFP() && (index_fp < 8)) {
5536  set_fpu_register(index_fp++, arg.bits());
5537  } else if (arg.IsFP() && (index_gp < 8)) {
5538  set_register(index_gp + 4, arg.bits());
5539  index_gp++;
5540  } else {
5541  DCHECK(arg.IsFP() || arg.IsGP());
5542  stack_args.push_back(arg.bits());
5543  }
5544  }
5545 
5546  // Remaining arguments passed on stack.
5547  int64_t original_stack = get_register(sp);
5548  // Compute position of stack on entry to generated code.
5549  int64_t stack_args_size = stack_args.size() * sizeof(stack_args[0]);
5550  int64_t entry_stack = original_stack - stack_args_size;
5551 
5552  if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() != 0) {
5553  entry_stack &= -base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
5554  }
5555  // Store remaining arguments on stack, from low to high memory.
5556  char* stack_argument = reinterpret_cast<char*>(entry_stack);
5557  memcpy(stack_argument, stack_args.data(),
5558  stack_args.size() * sizeof(int64_t));
5559  set_register(sp, entry_stack);
5560 
5561  CallInternal(entry);
5562 
5563  // Pop stack passed arguments.
5564  CHECK_EQ(entry_stack, get_register(sp));
5565  set_register(sp, original_stack);
5566 }
5567 
5568 double Simulator::CallFP(Address entry, double d0, double d1) {
5569  const FPURegister fparg2 = f1;
5570  set_fpu_register_double(f0, d0);
5571  set_fpu_register_double(fparg2, d1);
5572  CallInternal(entry);
5573  return get_fpu_register_double(f0);
5574 }
5575 
5576 uintptr_t Simulator::PushAddress(uintptr_t address) {
5577  int64_t new_sp = get_register(sp) - sizeof(uintptr_t);
5578  uintptr_t* stack_slot = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(new_sp);
5579  *stack_slot = address;
5580  set_register(sp, new_sp);
5581  return new_sp;
5582 }
5583 
5584 uintptr_t Simulator::PopAddress() {
5585  int64_t current_sp = get_register(sp);
5586  uintptr_t* stack_slot = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(current_sp);
5587  uintptr_t address = *stack_slot;
5588  set_register(sp, current_sp + sizeof(uintptr_t));
5589  return address;
5590 }

5592 Simulator::LocalMonitor::LocalMonitor()
5593  : access_state_(MonitorAccess::Open),
5594  tagged_addr_(0),
5595  size_(TransactionSize::None) {}
5596 
5597 void Simulator::LocalMonitor::Clear() {
5598  access_state_ = MonitorAccess::Open;
5599  tagged_addr_ = 0;
5600  size_ = TransactionSize::None;
5601 }
5602 
5603 void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyLoad() {
5604  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::RMW) {
5605  // A non linked load could clear the local monitor. As a result, it's
5606  // most strict to unconditionally clear the local monitor on load.
5607  Clear();
5608  }
5609 }
5610 
5611 void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyLoadLinked(uintptr_t addr,
5612  TransactionSize size) {
5613  access_state_ = MonitorAccess::RMW;
5614  tagged_addr_ = addr;
5615  size_ = size;
5616 }
5617 
5618 void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyStore() {
5619  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::RMW) {
5620  // A non exclusive store could clear the local monitor. As a result, it's
5621  // most strict to unconditionally clear the local monitor on store.
5622  Clear();
5623  }
5624 }
5625 
5626 bool Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyStoreConditional(uintptr_t addr,
5627  TransactionSize size) {
5628  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::RMW) {
5629  if (addr == tagged_addr_ && size_ == size) {
5630  Clear();
5631  return true;
5632  } else {
5633  return false;
5634  }
5635  } else {
5636  DCHECK(access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Open);
5637  return false;
5638  }
5639 }

5641 Simulator::GlobalMonitor::LinkedAddress::LinkedAddress()
5642  : access_state_(MonitorAccess::Open),
5643  tagged_addr_(0),
5644  next_(nullptr),
5645  prev_(nullptr),
5646  failure_counter_(0) {}
5647 
5648 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::LinkedAddress::Clear_Locked() {
5649  access_state_ = MonitorAccess::Open;
5650  tagged_addr_ = 0;
5651 }
5652 
5653 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::LinkedAddress::NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(
5654  uintptr_t addr) {
5655  access_state_ = MonitorAccess::RMW;
5656  tagged_addr_ = addr;
5657 }
5658 
5659 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::LinkedAddress::NotifyStore_Locked() {
5660  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::RMW) {
5661  // A non exclusive store could clear the global monitor. As a result, it's
5662  // most strict to unconditionally clear global monitors on store.
5663  Clear_Locked();
5664  }
5665 }
5666 
5667 bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::LinkedAddress::NotifyStoreConditional_Locked(
5668  uintptr_t addr, bool is_requesting_thread) {
5669  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::RMW) {
5670  if (is_requesting_thread) {
5671  if (addr == tagged_addr_) {
5672  Clear_Locked();
5673  // Introduce occasional sc/scd failures. This is to simulate the
5674  // behavior of hardware, which can randomly fail due to background
5675  // cache evictions.
5676  if (failure_counter_++ >= kMaxFailureCounter) {
5677  failure_counter_ = 0;
5678  return false;
5679  } else {
5680  return true;
5681  }
5682  }
5683  } else if ((addr & kExclusiveTaggedAddrMask) ==
5684  (tagged_addr_ & kExclusiveTaggedAddrMask)) {
5685  // Check the masked addresses when responding to a successful lock by
5686  // another thread so the implementation is more conservative (i.e. the
5687  // granularity of locking is as large as possible.)
5688  Clear_Locked();
5689  return false;
5690  }
5691  }
5692  return false;
5693 }
5694 
5695 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(
5696  uintptr_t addr, LinkedAddress* linked_address) {
5697  linked_address->NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(addr);
5698  PrependProcessor_Locked(linked_address);
5699 }
5700 
5701 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyStore_Locked(
5702  LinkedAddress* linked_address) {
5703  // Notify each thread of the store operation.
5704  for (LinkedAddress* iter = head_; iter; iter = iter->next_) {
5705  iter->NotifyStore_Locked();
5706  }
5707 }
5708 
5709 bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyStoreConditional_Locked(
5710  uintptr_t addr, LinkedAddress* linked_address) {
5711  DCHECK(IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(linked_address));
5712  if (linked_address->NotifyStoreConditional_Locked(addr, true)) {
5713  // Notify the other processors that this StoreConditional succeeded.
5714  for (LinkedAddress* iter = head_; iter; iter = iter->next_) {
5715  if (iter != linked_address) {
5716  iter->NotifyStoreConditional_Locked(addr, false);
5717  }
5718  }
5719  return true;
5720  } else {
5721  return false;
5722  }
5723 }
5724 
5725 bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(
5726  LinkedAddress* linked_address) const {
5727  return head_ == linked_address || linked_address->next_ ||
5728  linked_address->prev_;
5729 }
5730 
5731 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::PrependProcessor_Locked(
5732  LinkedAddress* linked_address) {
5733  if (IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(linked_address)) {
5734  return;
5735  }
5736 
5737  if (head_) {
5738  head_->prev_ = linked_address;
5739  }
5740  linked_address->prev_ = nullptr;
5741  linked_address->next_ = head_;
5742  head_ = linked_address;
5743 }
5744 
5745 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::RemoveLinkedAddress(
5746  LinkedAddress* linked_address) {
5747  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex);
5748  if (!IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(linked_address)) {
5749  return;
5750  }
5751 
5752  if (linked_address->prev_) {
5753  linked_address->prev_->next_ = linked_address->next_;
5754  } else {
5755  head_ = linked_address->next_;
5756  }
5757  if (linked_address->next_) {
5758  linked_address->next_->prev_ = linked_address->prev_;
5759  }
5760  linked_address->prev_ = nullptr;
5761  linked_address->next_ = nullptr;
5762 }
